  id: 860,
  header: "To know the sting of life",
  question:
    "Jai Shri Ram\n"+
    "While reading I came to know that we have 7 nos of strings to live our life, That farmer lady was having 13 sting, my question is that how many sting we can earn in our human life and how? Is there any maximum number?\n\n"+
    "Jai Hanuman Ji",
  answer:
    "Divine Soul,\n\n"+
    "Purpose of life should ideally be Moksha, not earning of Kaal strings. Moksha means settling all the Karma and desires and ultimately merging identity with the supreme. On the other hand, earning strings of time means accumulating positive Karmas. If you accumulate positive Karmas, you will ideally reach in VishnuLoka or you will become a Surrah at end of time.\n\n"+
    "In case of women, every string of time has strands on it. Those strands can be matured and become strings. A maximum of 4,20,000 strands can be matured into strings.\n\n"+
    "Apart from that, a person, be it man or woman, can earn strings from KaalDeva by doing good deeds. There is no maximum for that but it is hard to earn strings. There are two types of good deeds - (1) Good deeds by nature (2) Good deeds by purpose. If you do good deeds for purpose of earning strings of Time, you can't earn even a single string. If you do good deeds without any purpose, then you will earn strings of time.\n\n"+
    "---\n\n"+
    "While fighting the evil of this world, make sure that you don't get dragged down by the evil into the evil.\n\n"+
    "|| Ram ||"
