  id: 889,
  header: "Life and death",
  question:
    "1. The concept of 'everything is an illusion' is not new to us. Its the same moral in Bagvadgita more or less. So my doubt is if we want to treat everything as illusion then we have no life (as per our current understanding of life that we need to get educated, get a job, get married, have kids family and die). The feeling for others, feeling sad for people around who are suffering from different problems, shouldn't we feel for them? If all that is illusion, basically we are denying our own existence by questioning our emotions. Aren't we? Then what do we treat as actual life?\n\n"+
    "2. I lost my dad 21 months back. He was 50-51 years old. I still feel sad for him. I was not by his side during his last few days. I never cared whether God existed, so I did not pray for him when he fell ill. This makes me feel bad every time I think of my dad, and my family. I even cry today randomly. He never did any bad to anyone. Everyone who know him loves him. But why did he have to suffer? I know I did a lot of mistakes (non-veg, alcohol, girls, which is not allowed in my traditional home) in life and so I deserve to be punished and I am ready whatever happens to me. But the question that haunts me, Is my family/dad punished because of my karma? Do son's bad deeds hurt the father/family? Is there a way to know about my father's soul whereabouts? I feel like I owe him a lot. I owe him my entire life.\n\n"+
    "Please answer these two questions, in detail.",
  answer:
    "Divine Soul,\n\n"+
    "(1) It depends who \"you\" are? Are you a \"body\", \"mind\" and \"intellect\"? Or are you something higher than that? When you are indulged in this world, you are a human being which has a \"body\" which feels, \"mind\" which thinks and \"intellect\" which judges. But when you are not indulged in this world, you are a soul. You can switch from \"Body, mind, intellect\" to \"soul\" through silence or through curiosity. See, when you typed this question, you were thinking beyond \"body.mind,intellect\". You were watching yourself. The curiosity crawled you through intellect to something higher. May be you remained in that situation for a second and then came back to your body senses. There are no readymade answers for these questions. Answer can just help you to rise above body. Answer resides in brain. If you want to experience something beyond your body and brain, then you cannot stick to an answer. You can only experience that yourself.\n\n"+
    "(2) The soul of your father has taken birth again. But you cannot call her your father now. That soul has taken many births before also. And it will take few births more. Your father is with you in the form of memories. He is nowhere else. Your Karma did not affect him. It was his own destiny. You should also not hold on to your past. Nothing was in your control. Everything was destined to happen the way it happened. Your soul is still pure. Just ponder over the question \"Who I am\". You will realize that you are a pure soul.\n\n"+
    "Blessings"
