    question: "Namaskar, Sai Ram,\nI have been reading all the chapters posted on Setuu, and narrate them to my mother as well. We have had many divine experiences after reading the chapters. In many of the chapters, Mukti Sagara or the Ocean of Milk, on which Lord Vishnu reclines on the eternal Adi Shesha is described. It is described as a place that contains everything to fulfill all the desires of a soul. But how exactly is Mukti Sagara ? What lies below it ? Is it a kind of Loka or is it something different ?\nIn many scriptures, Adi Shakti is said to reside in a divine Loka called Akshara Dhama, where all Goddesses, kinnaris, yakshinis, gandharvis, also live. Where is this Akshara Dhama then ? Is it even above Vaikuntha and Mukti Sagara ?\n\nPranams,\nJai Shri Ram, Jai Bajrangbali Hanumaan !\n\nJai Sai Maa.",
