    question: "...the very first time, I heard my inner prayer was the following sloka...\n\nअसाध्य साधक स्वामिन असाध्य तव किंवद |\nराम दूत कृपा सिंधो मत्कार्यं साध्यप्रभो ||\n\nThis was in the year 2001, I remember reciting this sloka as a child. My life had taken a lot of turns and 2001 was a very very important phase in my life. I was searching for a lot of answers in life. I felt purposeless, I felt useless and at that point in time was seriously contemplating suicide. This evening, I clearly remember praying, begging that there would be some hint, some indication that my life would be OK.\n\nAnd I heard the above prayer. I didn't even know what it really meant and asked my friend/spiritual brother its meaning. When he gave me the meaning, I immediately cried and understood that my life was going to start becoming better.\n\nIn a weird way, it felt as if, in the lowest point of my life, I felt like Lord Hanuman extended His grace to me. I am so grateful for that evening. I still remember it so clearly. Even now, when I think about that moment, I cry.\n\nMy life has been generally OK since. But, I spiritual life has twists and turns. I have made many mistakes. Just like Baba Matang says in Chapter 2, my circumstances drive a lot of things in my life. I wish to return to India and start over. I'm getting married next month. I wish to have the Lord's Darshan sometime and simply fall at His feet.\n\nFew days back, when I deep in meditation, I had a vision of a Monkey applying tilak on my forehead. There is a part of me that believes this is only because of Lord Hanuman. At times, I feel that I am forcefully imagining such visions. I would like see HIM for real just once.\n\nEven now, as I type this text, I feel the vibrations of my room have changed so much. Please Lord, I wish to see You. Please purify me enough so I can see YOU. Please Please Please."
