    question: "I am Suneil Mehta staying in Delhi. I am youngest in a family of 5 brothers and only sister.\n\nFew years now, some one advised me to read 108 Hunaman Challisa in one Sitting. I was not aware that my father was not well during that time as he was not staying with us due to many reasons. In Dec. 2009 - 10 I read 108 Challisa in morning session.\n\nIt is due Shri Hanumanji blessing, my father started new journey of life and left us within 24 hours of my chanting of Hanuman Challisa for 108 times.\n\nI am regularly worshiping Shri Hanumanji, visiting Temples on Tuesday and Saturday for prayers to Shri Hanumanji.\n\nI feel he is very much with us. Hunaman Mandir in Connaught Place, New Delhi is the place where my family ( my wife, son and me) do regularly visit in Good and Bad times. I have suggested many to do 108 chant of Hanuman Challisa who ever facing any big troubles.\n\nBajrang Bali ki Jai, Pawan sut Shri Hanuman ki Jay.\n\nSuneil Mehta"
