    answer: "Divine Soul,\n\nThe emotions behind this prayer has been acknowledged.\n\nExcerpts from the conversation between Gods and Brahmins in Sakshat Hanuman Pooja ---\n\n\"Once two souls rose from the MuktiSagara and expressed desire to see wonders of ocean in MaanavLoka (human world). Lord Vishnu granted their wish and sent them on Maanavloka. They took birth as twins in home of a fisherman. When they grew and explored the ocean, they saw big fishes eating small fishes in ocean. And they saw fishes being eaten by human beings. One child got sympathetic about the beautiful creatures of ocean and another child thought, \"Big fishes eat small fishes in the ocean. This is law of this universe. This is how God made this world. Hence humans should also enjoy eating the creatures of ocean.\" He became expert in catching fish. He would venture far into the sea and catch different types of fishes. The another child used to cry on seeing fishes getting killed by big fishes and human beings. He would cry and pray to God to stop all this.\n\nAfter some time, Lord Vishnu sent message to those souls, \"O souls, you desired to see the ocean and now that your desires have been fulfilled, why don't you return?\"\n\nSurprisingly none of them could hear the message of Lord Vishnu. One child was indulged in catching fishes while another child was indulged in sympathy. Their indulgence in the mortal world made them deaf to message of Lord Vishnu.\n\nAfter few days a monk came to fisherman's house. The child who was sympathetic towards fishes expressed his desire to leave home and go with the monk. He went with the monk and soon got Moksha and returned to Vishnumoka. Another child was so indulged in catching fishes that he has accumulated lots of Karma in taking birth after birth. That child is still here on earth\"\n\n-----------\nDivine Soul of Raghav,\nAs you can infer from this story, sympathy is also a form of indulgence in mortal world. But the benefit of sympathy is that it will lead you to supreme knowledge and soon will get you Moksha. On the other hand people who are indulged in evil will remain trapped till end and then they will become Asurrahs.\n\nBlessings"
