    id: 1178,
    header: "NEED GUIDANCE",
    question: "Pranam Guruji,\n\nI am communicating with you as last hope in my life.Please bear with me.\n\nMy life since childhood was never normal. Till date my life is full of struggle,loneliness.I have got issues in almost all sphere of life like studies,job,finance,personal etc.I continued my life without complain but now its becoming worst than earlier.I am married (already 36) for 9 years with no kids.we went for many infertility treatments but no success.on the advice of a priest we even went to a famous shrine in south ( Tirupathi & Kalashathi) to perform \"kaalsharp puja\" but still nothing has changed & infact things have become worst for me.no support from my parents and also from in laws. No peace in my life neither from my in laws nor from my parents side.Even my younger sister is issue less (5 years marriage) & youngest sister is still unmarried (she is 31 already).\nNo one has got time for us,not even god. have done lots of prayers but now at this age I understood that \"god doesn't help everyone\".\nI dont have job so nothing to divert my attention. I just want to know some solution for my sufferings.\nMy father is a Hanuman devotee & even I am reading hanuman chalisa for the past 1.5 year. After chanting hanuman chalisa I have become emotionally strong but my problems are still same,no solution why?\n\n1. will I be blessed with motherhood at least in this life?\n2. I have been chanting vishnu sahasranama,hanuman chalisa,ramayan for many years but why is that none of my puja shows any effect.are this prayers really effective or just a lie.\n\nits a pain to live life like this.wonder how long I can continue like this. I have been praying to shirdi Saibaba for last 10 years but now I feel cheated. In a sudden way I started praying to lord Hanuman for last 2 years (dont know how,no one ever asked me to pray to him).\n\nI feel completely LOST in life,dont know what to do & where to go.I have tried talking to lord Hanuman so many times but have not got any response. At least you can ask bhagwan about me. nowadays very often I feel like committing suicide as this is the only solution for my problems.",
    answer: "Divine Soul,\n\nDesires may get blocked for a number of reasons. An ordinary human being thinks that Gods can clear the blockage instantly. That is not true. If you have read Leelas of Lord Hanuman in chapters published so far, you must have realized that Gods also work within the framework of laws which run this universe.\n\nThere is a certain trap called the Mire Gridlock. More Gods try to blockage in such a gridlock, more new blockages come up. That is partly caused by the soul itself. You need to cooperate in order for Gods to be able to clear the blockages. Here are a few things you can do from your side:\n\nYour soul has already expressed your desire to the universe. Don't repeat that desire again and again otherwise things get complicated for Indra Deva. If you see your desire getting fulfilled in SwapanLoka, you can repeat your desire again after waking up. Otherwise don't repeat your desire.\n\nRepeating desire doesn't only mean speaking with your mouth or thinking. You are expressing this desire hundreds of times everyday. You know how? Your single desire has affected your entire outlook. It is showing its influence in every single thing you do. To make things simple for Indra Deva, you have to do your Karmas as if you don't have this unfulfilled desire loaded at your back.\n\nAlso, don't let your mind be in the fear that 'what if the desire doesn't get fulfilled. What if I don't become mother.' If you have this fear, you have Asurrahs around you and where there are Asurrahs, Gods cannot help you. It is up to the soul to stay aware and not let Asurrahs take over body-mind. It is not Gods' duty to shoo away Asurrahs.\n\nOne way to stay free from fear is to think about an alternative. You should think like, 'No problem if my desire doesn't get fulfilled. I can adopt someone'. Or any other alternative you can think of.\n\nIn chapter 3, the mother was in fear and desperation. Lord Hanuman had a solution in mind but that lady's desperation was not letting Gods apply the solution. So Lord Hanuman played a trick. It looked as though the child died. Then that lady broke down and her desperation flew away. Then Gods applied their solution.\n\nThere are many such concepts discussed in the chapters published so far. If you read these chapters not with the purpose of desire fulfillment but for purpose of true knowledge, you will get many solutions and suggestions from there. Apply those suggestions.\n\nMay your desire gets fulfilled very soon."
