    question: "Jai Shree Ram\nJai Sita Maiya\nJai Bajrangbali\n\nLord Hanuman, you know everything. You know very well what my current situation is. I am not understanding what to do. I have been in a different city searching for a good job for around 9 months, but I have got nothing. In March 2016, it will be one year since I lost my job.\n\nI really don't understand why I am not getting a good job. Are my Karmas not enough to get a good job? Do I need to work harder? Has the time not come yet for my job? Do I need to wait for some more time? I really don't know the reasons behind this. Now, I doubt my decision of changing my field from Electrical (Phd & teaching) to IT Industry. Sometimes I think hadn't I changed my field, I would have got a job in teaching or I must have joined for Phd.\n\nLord Hanuman, I really don't understand what to do now. Please show me the way. At least, give me some hints. What should I do? Shall I continue my job search in IT Industry or I switch to teaching or Phd or I prepare for government jobs? Please show me some way.\n\nMy parents have consulted some astrologers and pandits. They all after seeing my horoscope say different different things. Some say that I should try in government sector as I have the 'Yog' of government job in my horoscope. While others say that private sector is best for me and I have 'Yog' of going to some foreign countries. Some say that I should not try for government job as my 'Surya' is weak in my 'Kundali'. Different people say different adverse planetary effects. They all say different different adverse planetary effects. One even told my parents that I am not getting job because I am not applying for any job and I do nothing. While others say that it will take some more time. While others suggest for some Poojas. My parents have already done many Poojas for my job on their suggestions only but I think nothing is working. I am still jobless. They have done many Poojas to nullify the adverse planetary effects on their suggestions only. Also, they have given me some 'Yantras' to wear in my neck or hand and some 'Gemstones' too. I don't know how much they worked or are working. But I must say even after all this I don't have peace of mind.\n\nLord Hanuman, its high time. Now, I must get a good job and settle in life. Time is running very fast. I don't know what you have written in my destiny. I don't know what my fate is. But I have full faith in you. I have surrendered myself to you completely. Whatever you will do, it will be good for me (my soul). Lord Hanuman, please fulfill all my wishes. Let me be happy and content. O Hanumanji, please fulfill all my worldly desires so that I concentrate fully on attaining Moksha after fulfilling all my worldly responsibilities.\n\nSetuu, I am doing everything whatever you told me. Now, I don't bring my parents in my prayers. Now, I don't compare myself with anyone. I don't bother about what relatives and society say about me. I am working on each and every thing which you told me. Now, I try to be fearless and try not to think much about future. I have surrendered myself completely to Lord Hanuman. But as a normal human being I do think about my future, about my ambitions in life and about my responsibilities which I should fulfill in life. Although I think about these in my mind but I always try to connect my soul with Lord Hanuman. I am working on your suggestion that let body and mind do their work and I should connect to Lord Hanuman with my soul.\n\nI request the respected Mathangs to pray to Lord Hanuman for my job in Sakshat Hanuman Pooja.\n\nHere, I would also like to tell you that I have participated in Charan Pooja of Lord Hanuman and the Pooja was performed for me on May 13, 2014. If you need my Pooja Log number, please let me know. I am saying all this just because it may help you in knowing something about me. Please pardon me if I made any mistakes.\n\nI ask for forgiveness from Lord Hanuman for all my mistakes and misdeeds which I may have committed either knowingly or unknowingly either in my present birth or in previous births. Please forgive me Lord and keep your blessings on me forever.\n\nWaiting anxiously for a reply.\n\nPranam.",
