    header: "NOTHING BUT EVERYTHING, EVERYTHING BUT NOTHING",
    question: "The title says how confused I am. I have a good interest in spirituality and should also say, have passion for things that are abstract in nature (as psycology). I am not any good at it though. I sincerely read all the chapters here and I love the perspectives it has given me (and am thankful for the opportunity/blessing to read).\n\nI like to say that I love Lord Ram and wish one day he would be our son. I have a belief that Hanuman is my guru as he would help me love Ram more. As a teen, I used think that I could be kalki's mother since I love him so much and he would come to me. Now that I have become an adult and would always love him as my son, seeing my impurities makes me feel sad and I continue to beg Lord to hold my hand (and stay close) and forgive me as how a mother would forgive a child for his/her wrongdoings and gently guide them. I need Lord Ram/Seeta mata to forgive me as their child and guide me gently so I could have the pleasure of being their mother :)\n\nNeedless to say, I overthink which is good and bad. As much as I would like to be attached to Him, I do know that I am not religious enough to do timely prayers. I still think about Him throughout the day and tell Him that I love him as I love my daughter but I certainly don't do a good job at our prayer room or reciting slogas.\n\nI have a ton of flaws inside me, but I try not to do things for others that I do not want to experience myself. I tend to have endless dreams and generally tend to have a very disturbed sleep. If I regularly meditate and try to immerse myself in His thoughts (without all the everything fascinating/distracting things of modern world), I tend to have dreams in which I discover him underground, from sea etc.. As much as these dreams feel divine, I also have scary/no-sense dreams when my mind is occupied/influenced by thoughts in modern world (I mean thoughts not spiritual in nature).\n\nReading the chapters was a divine feeling and such opportunities help me not to overly deviate from spiritual path (or simply how I am supposed to be). With knowing about asurahs and surahs (and co-relation to dreams), I wonder if I am hijacked by them every second, if I have the ability to own anything for myself to offer Him.\n\nI do understand this isn't something to think with my brain, but its painful to realize I am not being good enough. The part in 8th chapter that said mother of Kalki has to be so pure to remain uninfuenced but surah/asurah made me feel so sad. I might not be close at all or crazy to think that way, but its painful to see how I am and how His mother really would be.\n\nI also believe if I say I am going to change from now on and become good enough, then it would really be my ego that's talking. I do believe even the blessing to love Him needs to come from Him. I like things that are aesthetically appealing and have quite a bit (including my impulsive purchases for it) - I do understand they mean nothing and the nature provided by Him and Him are the most aesthetically beautiful and appealing things in the world. I have a very unsettling brain struggling to realize something that is the ultimate truth and beauty (and when tired of search resorts to beautiful things in materialistic world (from very simple things like my dresses, ear rings and bags). I do believe everything is a representation of Him and its the same energy everywhere presenting Him but just have a hard time experiencing it.\n\nI don't really know what to ask for, I guess I just want the blessing to stop asking and realize the contentment and oneness in everything. The only constant thing I ever want to wish for is being His mother and see Him happy (I feel sad for what Ram/Seeta had to go thru). and wish for Hanuman's forgiveness for not being very sincere in things I need to be and for all the thoughts I tend to accumulate in the materialistic world because of disillusionment.\n\nPlease submit my forgiveness and Love to Him and my prayers for more motherly love for Him. I would really be grateful for a reply (for my satisfaction) and would like to understand about significance of dreams and path for realizing Him (significance of religious practices vs just loving Him as one would love their close ones).\n\nBless everyone around me and my family and this world. Save people from hunger, disasters and cruelty. SRIRAMAJAYAM. Could I ever see Hanuman and become Ram's mother? Sarvam is an arpanam to Him."
