    id: 1229,
    header: "PENDING DESIRES OF PREVIOUS BIRTHS",
    question: "Jai Shree Ram\nJai Sita Maiya\nJai Bajrangbali\n\nPlease accept my sincere Pranam.\n\nWhen we desire something, the universe works for fulfilling it according to the Law of Trideva. If our Karmas are sufficient, then, our desires get fulfilled else they get transferred to our next births. Lord Indra tells that he can wait till infinity to fulfill our desires if we don't put a time limit on it. But if we put a time limit and our Karmas are not sufficient, then he dumps them in Swapanloka. Also, when Lord Indra makes sure that a certain dream can't be fulfilled in Manavloka, then also he dumps it in Swapanloka. So, if we don't put a time limit on our desires, then, they will be transferred to our next births too. In this way, we can have numerous pending desires from previous births and present birth. And in this way we will be taking births again and again to fulfill those desires from previous births. It's just like a cyclic process.\n\nWe humans don't have memories of previous births. We don't remember what we had desired in previous births. Lord Indra dumps hundreds of our desires everyday in our SwapanLoka which we even don't remember.\n\nWhen Dhanushka asked Lord Indra, isn't there any way to get rid of all pending desires, then, Lord Indra answered him to do Karmas, the same Karmas which are required to get Moksha and don't express any more desire.\n\nHere, my question is same what Dhanushka asked Lord Indra.\n\nIs it possible for people of mainstream society like us that we don't desire anything? I mean to say that we live in such a world where we need certain things to survive. We have so many responsibilities and to fulfill them, we need good job, money etc. Just consider my case only. I have completed my masters and looking for a good, permanent and stable job. And all these come under desire. Is it bad to desire for a good, permanent and stable job and a good lifestyle? Is it bad to have desire of the basic necessities which are essential for survival in today's world?\n\nHere, I have become very much confused. I need your help. I want to get rid of pending desires of my previous births. Please tell me how can I get rid of pending desires of my previous births and useless desires of present birth too or tell me any way that they just get dumped in Swapanloka by Lord Indra. I request Lord Hanuman and Lord Indra to dump my pending desires of previous births and useless desires of present birth too in Swapanloka so that they don't affect my life in Manavloka.\n\nPlease pardon me if I asked anything wrong. I am just a small bhakt of Lord Hanuman who is following this website like anything and wait for the next chapter very anxiously. I want to fulfill all my responsibilities (Karmas) for which I have taken birth and then move towards Moksha.\n\nThanks and regards.\n\nJai Shree Ram\nJai Sita Maiya\nJai Bajrangbali",
    answer: "Divine Soul,\n\nWhen we express ourselves, we use the word \"I\" many times. In the expression we assume that \"I\" is self defined. But it is not. Who do you mean when you say \"I\"? Giving up desires is giving up the lower \"I\" and shifting to higher \"I\". This part cannot be explained right now. Please wait for upcoming chapters.\n\nBlessings"
