    answer: "Divine Soul,\n\nIf the desire has been dumped in SwapanLoka, you have renewed it the very next morning by thinking about that dream. So the desire still remains.\n\nDo Karma as per your Dharma or the set of principles on which you live your life. Every human being must set a Dharma for himself/herself and do everything according to Dharma. You should think as a free person, as a person with no desire and set a Dharma principle, like to what extent you want to go to fulfill your desire to be with ******. Set a Dharma principle so that you don't regret anything in future. You can say, 'whatever I did, I did as per my Dharma. So I have no regrets no matter the outcome.'\n\nYou do not need to know your future. Act as per your Dharma.\n\nBlessings"
