    question: "Jai Bajrangbali\nJai Shree Ram\n\nThank you Setuu for connecting souls like me with lord Hanuman. I really feel that I am very lucky that I participated in \"Charan Pooja\" through Setuu which happens only once in 41 years. I have the opportunity to participate in \"Sakshant Hanuman Pooja\" also. I must say I have the blessings of lord Hanuman.\n\nI am a regular visitor of this site. I have written here many experiences, thoughts and questions and have got proper answers and directions. And I think this interaction will continue in future too.\n\nI have lost my job and am looking for a good permanent job. I have done graduation(B.Tech) in Electrical & Electronics Engineering and post graduation(M.E) in Electrical Engineering. I was working in a reputed software company but I lost my job.\n\nPlease help me in choosing my career Hanumanji.\n\nAs I am a Post Graduate, I have more than one option to choose from for my career. This is creating problem to me in choosing my career. I am really very confused. I am not able to concentrate on one thing. So many thoughts come to my mind. I am not able to decide which field is good for me. Please help me Hanumanji.\n\nSometimes, I think I can go for PhD or I join some engineering college as an Assistant Professor and go for PhD later or I can complete my PhD part time being an Assistant Professor.\n\nSometimes I think to prepare for government jobs like Bank, SSC etc while sometimes I think to go for IES and PSUs like Sail, Bhel, Ntpc etc.\n\nWhile sometimes I think to go in software or IT sector like Infosys, TCS, etc where I was working.\n\nRight now, I am planning to go to Bangalore for studying and searching job in IT field. I don't know whether this would be good for me or not. I have opted for software just because I was working in software earlier and one of my friends suggested me the same. Although I am planning to go to Bangalore but I am not sure whether my decision is right or not. I am very much confused. I am not getting peace of mind. Please keep your blessings on me always Hanumanji.\n\nHanumanji, you know everything past, present and future. Please help me in deciding which field should I choose. You know what is best for me. Please help in choosing such a field in which I get a good, permanent and stable job. I really want a good and stable job.\n\nI strongly feel that Hanumanji will bless me with a good, permanent and stable job very soon. I have full faith in lord Hanuman and there is no place for fear and worry in my heart and mind when Hanumanji is with me.\n\nI request the Mathangs to ask Hanumanji in Sakshat Hanuman Pooja regarding which field should I go and which field would be best for me. Also, I request the Mathangs to pray to lord Hanuman on my behalf for my job.\n\nHanumanji, please forgive me for my misdeeds or mistakes which I have made either in this birth or previous births. Keep your blessings on me always.\n\nThank you Setuu\nThank you Mathangs\nRegards",
    answer: "Divine Soul,\n\nThere is a thing called \"Dharma\". A human being has to take all his/her decisions according to their Dharma. Dharma cannot be defined in general because it is different for different people. Dharma brings a sense of responsibility in every action of human being. For example, suppose a person took a decision to the best of his/her intellect. Suppose that decision did not yield the result he/she wanted and he/she realizes that had he taken another decision, things would have been different. At this point that person will not repent if he has followed his Dharma. He would think, \"I took a decision as per my Dharma. I have no remorse if that decision has gone wrong.\" This is the power of Dharma in human life. It brings responsibility in every action.\n\nYou have come on mortal world to settle your past Karma. Decision has to be yours and only yours.\n\nBlessings"
