    answer: "Divine Soul,\n\nThese are human emotions. These emotions make you a human being. If you acquire a sense of detachment, these emotions will not trouble you. To acquire detachment, practice observing yourself. The best part of being a human is that you can switch the observer as per your will.\n\nImagine a person who is crying because of his loved ones. You are observing that person and that person is in turn observing his loved ones. He is crying because he is hurt by his loved ones. Will you also start crying when you see that person? No. Because you are detached from that person.\n\nIn the similar way, you can detach yourself from your mind. In your case, who is getting hurt? Your mind. You start observing your mind as a third person. Then you will not feel the hurt.\n\nNow starts the magic! When you get detached, you will find that your loved ones are behaving the way you want! But please note, do not detach from your loved ones. Detach only from your mind. Let your mind feel all the emotions. But you should remain detached from your mind.\n\nWho are you? You are a soul. You are not a mind. Neither are you a body.\n\nLord Hanuman's blessings are with you."
