    header: "QUERY",
    question: "jai shri ram..\n\ni have two queries\n\n1. \" jug shashtra joajn par bhanu\nlilyo tahi madhur fal janu\" this is a couplet from hanuman chalisa... my query is about truthness of this couplet.. did it actually happened?? and do hanuman chalisa makes him happy??\n\n2. this one is not that important though i would like clear the doubt, i have read it at too many sites on internet that hanuman ji is not monkey?? please clear the doubts.. regards.. jai shree ram...",
    answer: "Divine Soul,\n\nThe way you perceive it and the way it happened can be different. Human beings of Kaliyuga has a very objective thinking. They perceive that the Sun is an object and Lord Hanuman jumped over to the sun and ate it. It is not as simple as that. However the couplet is true. It is very difficult to make you understand at this point. If you have read third chapter, you may get a little idea of how things actually are. What a mortal being can see around himself is very limited version of reality. There are many more things which mortal beings cannot see. Lord Hanuman is not bonded by Time. For Him, 1 kilometer is as distant as 1 million kilometers. He is not bonded by space also. For Him, an apple is as big as the sun OR the sun is as small as apple. It may be very difficult for you to understand this but keep reading the chapters of His journey as we post them here. You will be able to see the larger reality very soon. Chanting of Hanuman Chalisa makes you closer to Lord Hanuman. It is not about Him being happy. It is about how close your soul is with Lord Hanuman. \"Happiness\" is an objective thing. Lord Hanuman lies way beyond happiness and unhappiness. Lord Hanuman never hurts His devotees. He is never unhappy with His devotees. If you go in the direction shown by the Lord, YOU will be happy because you will not meet any problem. If you go in wrong direction, you shall face problems. That does not mean that problems are created by Lord Hanuman. Those problems are because you are on the wrong path where Lord Hanuman is not there to save you from problems.\n\nLord Hanuman can take any form now. Monkey is one of His forms. It is wrong to say that \"He is not monkey\". Human beings have built the false perception that monkey is a \"lesser\" mortal or monkey is \"brainless\" etc etc. Monkey is closer to God than a human being of Kaliyuga. If somebody is making a joke about Lord Hanuman saying that He is a monkey, there is no need for devotees to become defensive and to try building logic to prove that \"Lord Hanuman is not monkey\". Monkey is not a lesser mortal.\n\nBlessings"
