    question: "Jai Shree Ram\nJai Sita Maiya\nJai Bajrangbali\n\nReally it's difficult for the people of mainstream society to understand chapter-9. For understanding it, we need to go beyond human minds and this is exactly what I tried to do. I don't know how much I succeeded in doing so. But I feel I succeeded in doing it.\n\nI have a question regarding the ridge in the sea. I know that there is a difference between the time coordinates of Maanav Lok and Paatal Lok. The seer of Paatal Lok can see only the past of Maanav Lok and not present and future. When the creatures of Paatal Lok (Ahi and Mahi) abducted the supreme soul of Lord Ram and Lakshman, the war had already started and they had already built the bridge over sea. But the creatures of Paatal Lok sent the enforcement which formed the ridge in the sea after the seer of Paatal Lok talked with the supreme soul of Lord Ram, then, how could the ridge got formed earlier? My doubt is related to time coordinates of Maanav Lok and Paatal Lok. How could the ridge appear in the sea before the creatures of Paatal Lok could send enforcement? When the ridge got formed in the sea, at that time, supreme soul of Lord Ram and Lakshman were not abducted by creatures of Paatal Lok, then, how could the ridge was formed in the see much before their abduction and without any enforcement by the creatures of Paatal Lok.\n\nPlease clear my doubt.\n\nI have one more question. Is this bridge man made or natural? The ridge was formed by the enforcement of the creatures of Paatal Lok and the ridge was filled and made even surface by Nal.\n\nChapter-9 is really very interesting which takes us beyond human minds. I am really blessed that I am getting Brahm Gyan from lord Hanuman himself with the efforts of Setuu. Please accept my sincere Pranam Setuu.\n\nThanks and regards.",
