    header: "REGARDING SWAPNALOKA AND THE JOURNEY OF THE SOUL",
    question: "Namaste,\n\nI came to know from one of the chapters that swapnaloka is far away from this material world and we enter swapnaloka with our soul .\nBut , if our soul enters the swapnaloka leaving the body behind , does it mean we are dead for that time? As far as I know soul is the driving force or chaitanya for the body . But, if it leaves the body and enters swapna loka , what about the body's existence then?\n\nPlease explain.\n\nThanking you,\nMabikanta Gcvs",
