    id: 1592,
    header: "SOUL SHYAM",
    question: "Thank you Lord Hanumanji for the deep knowledge that you have bestowed on us in relation to the different world and how our soul travels in each world.\nI have a query in your narration of Nala travel to Pataal Lok.\nWhen Nal went to Pataal Lok, the war had already started and the army had crossed the bridge made by Nal on the ridge. How can the Pataal Lok people make the ridge, the knowledge of which they came to know regarding Tearing apart, in their present time for an event which has already taken place in the past, in Maanav Lok.\nOr was it that the crocodile who had seen Nal in the sea had gone and arranged the Ridge.\nThanks for the knowledge and supporting the Setu.",
    answer: "Divine Soul,\n\nThis is illusion of Time. If you can recognize this illusion, you will become very close to Lord Hanuman, But it is not easy to recognize it, Efforts have to be made by you only. Read the chapter and think deep. Everything is explained in chapter 9. Not even a single more word is required to understand this mystery. What is required is that you should abandon the human perspective and acquire some more perspectives.\n\nA devotee had similar doubt. He spoke with the Setuu Masters and see how he realized it. This conversation may help you :\n\nDevotee :  I been reading each and every chapter constantly, i have one big question\nafter reading chapter 9 , please try to get me the answer. As per the chapter9, stone stayed firmed on water because there was one long layer created, but this layer was created when God Ram & God Lakshman's soul was kidnapped during the War in Lanka, then Drashta created this layer by modifying the past so the question is , how did God Ram and Laxman reached for the first time in Lanka as they were already in war, then past was modified , I hope you got my question? Please answer this one, i am keen to understand this.\n\nSetuu Masters : Divine Soul,\n\nWe are the upperworld for Paatal, so we see their future. And Paatal is lower world for Bhuloka, so they see our past.\n\nSuppose that you have a machine through which you can see Paatal. Imagine that you are on the beach when Nala has gone to survey the sea. What would you see in Paatal? You will see that Lord Ram and Laxman's souls are there and Drashta is interrogating them.\n\nNow suppose that you are in Paatal and you have a machine through which you can see Bhuloka. Imagine that you are in the hall where drashta is interrogating souls of Lord Ram and Laxman. If you see Bhuloka from there through your machine, what will you see? You will see that Nala is surveying the sea.\n\nProblem with your analysis is that you are choosing a observation point which is neither in Paatal nor in Bhuloka. You are choosing a third world from where you see both Paatal and Bhuloka side by side. If you want to do that, you should first know what is the relationship of that third world with Paatal and Bhuloka. Then you need to factor in that relationship in your analysis.\n\nBlessings\n\nDevotee : Still one doubt , i can see from bholok the future where bhagwan ram getting interoggated and due to that a long stripe was build upon whom rocks were standing but that is future , what i understood is future at patal ishappening in current of bholok ,how that is possible?? Or i again missed some point.\n\nSetuu Masters : Divine Soul,\n\nTake out a paper and draw three points on it : Paatal, Bhulok and Observation point. To keep things simple, bring your observation point either to Paatal or Bhulok. This is about relativity : If you change your observation point, observation will change. Hence you cannot move observation point at your convenience, otherwise you will get absurd observations.\n\nWrite down your every thought and identify the observation point of that thought. You will find out the error in your observations.\n\nRemember, you are not a fixed object when you are doing a thought experiment. In thought experiment, your mind is free to go anywhere. Keep a check on where your mind is situated while making an observation.\n\nBlessings\n\nDevotee : Super awesome concept, this means it was leela of Bhagwan vishu, sukhracharya felt he was creating conspiracy to kidnap rama, infact it was leela of god which was in other word helping him in creating bridge ... My God :) Regards"
