    header: "SUPREME LORD- KRISHNA",
    question: "Dear Setuu,\n\nSai Ram\nJai Hanuman,\n\nAccept my humble pranamas to you and all the Mathangs.\nIt was really nice to know how the benevolent Krishna made accommodation in the universe for sudama as his childhood friend. He says very clearly that HE can go beyond any limitations for his bhaktas who remembers him, sings his glory, offer oblation,etc with true devotion.\n\nI have a prayer request. My son is starting his 10th standard this academic year. Please pray for him and bless him that he does well in this journey.\n\nAlong with the above, I have the following questions.\n1) How many days will Lord Hanuman spend with the Mathangs when he visits them in 41 years?\n2) I want to know in brief about sakshat Hanuman pooja done by Setuu.(as told by Hanuman till the coming of Kalki avatar)\n3) When a devotee sends an arpanam, does the arpanam happen in the same manner as explained in the log book of Mathangs (like removing negative karma).(I am just anxious. Wanting to know was there a fruit or a piece which was eligible for arpanam)\n4) Why did Lord Hanuman get angry (a little bit) on Janakirupa? Is it because she didn't get the cue from the lord that she is going get back the gemstone, if she has love to the lord OR she was asking for a materialist desire?\n\nLastly thank you for all your support and prayers. Truly Setuu stands by its name and work as a bridge between soul and super soul.",
    answer: "Divine Soul,\n\nWhen we try to understand things which are beyond perception of mind, we encounter various paradoxes. If you have read the chapters so far sincerely, you will understand the paradoxes of time and space. \"how many days\" is a question which tends to project something beyond Time on the scale of Time. We can get that projection, but it would be only a projection. That projection is like a shadow. Depending on the position of Sun, your shadow varies in size. Similarly, every time we try to project Lord Hanuman's activities on the scale of Time, we get different projections.\n\nSakshat Hanuman Pooja is different from Charan Pooja in the sense that, in Charan Pooja Lord Hanuman's physical presence is there but in Sakshat Hanuman Pooja only His angelic presence is there. The Arpanam procedure is same. In Sakshat Hanuman Pooja, we try to decipher the chapters of Leelas which have been already enacted so as to get clue about the Lord Kalki's arrival. Prayers and Queries of devotees are also read and meditated upon in Sakshat Hanuman Pooja.\n\nLord Hanuman did not get angry. He only brought anger on His face so that Janakirupa couls give up her earrings without showing any attachment. Had Janakirupa showed even a little bit of attachment while wearing off the earrings, Lord Hanuman's Leela of bringing absolute change about existence of earrings may have got affected.\n\nBlessings"
