    question: "Namaste Setuu,\n\nJai Sri Ram.\n\nJai Sri Hanuman.\n\nI have already read all 12 chapters after reading each lots of things in my mind are cleared.\n\nIn fact I am devotee of Shiva every day I pray him to guide me for meditation and mukti (Moksha) and finally Shiva answer my prayer, I came in contact with setuu.org.\n\nI still have many confusion in mind about present-day life style. Here I want know 2 things.\n\n1) about Veg food and non-veg food.\n\nWhy in some religious eating non-veg is good event they offer non-veg foods in prayer.\nWhat kind of food human should in veg or non veg and why?\n\n2) about kundalini meditation practice.\n\nIs kundalini activation can be done? How? Is it good practice?\n\nSomewhere I listened they kundalini activation is nastic and challenge gods powers.\n\nWaiting for reply.\n\nThank you.\n\nJai Sri Ram.\n\nOm namah Shivay.",
    answer: "Divine Soul,\n\nTo get Moksha and to know supreme truth, one must rise from the level of body-mind to the level of soul. Animals live at the level of body. Most humans live at the level of body and mind. Some human beings also rise to the level of intellect and Samskara. But only very few human beings live at the level of soul. Who stops them from rising to the level of soul? Some activities of body-mind obstruct them and tie them to the level of body-mind. These activities may include eating certain kinds of food and other pleasure of senses. That is why Gurus advise seekers to avoid pleasure of senses. If any kind of food or beverage makes you Tamsik, you should avoid it.\n\nIt varies from person to person, place to place. For example, in some hot places people drink wine for pleasure of senses but at cold places wine is a necessity. Same is the case about veg and non-veg food. If somebody is living near the sea from childhood, for him fish is like a potato. It is not a pleasure for him, it is necessity. And eating fish doesn't destroy their human sensitivities. So they can rise to level of soul even when they are eating fish. So it depends on the environment in which you have grown up. There are no global do's and don's as far as food is concerned. You should decide for yourself whether a particular food is hindering your way to the higher self.\n\nThere can be many methods for rising to the level of soul. Kundalini meditation may be one of them. You should decide whether it works for you or not. At Setuu, we suggest the Gnana Marga through reading of Lord Hanuman's Leelas.\n\nBlessings"
