    header: "WHY ALL THIS IS HAPPENING TO ME",
    question: "Greetings.\n\nI am a very small and ignorant bhakt of Lord Hanuman. Please forgive me if I ask anything which I should have not asked.\n\nEver since I completed my masters, I was looking for a good job. After waiting for about six months, I got a job with God's grace. Although the job was not from my core field, I was very happy that I got a job. I thought God has given me this very job thinking something. I went with God's will and accepted the job and joined. I thought let's join the job given by God and God will make everything good.\n\nBut after joining the job I am facing lots of problem. I find it very tough to save my job. My training is going on right now. But I am not able to pass my exams in two attempts. Now only one attempt is left for me. I don't know the reasons behind my failure. I am trying hard to pass the exam. But the outcome is not in my favour.\n\nI don't know why all this is happening to me. If God has to take away my job then why did he give me this very job. I am really not understanding this. It's not that I am not trying to save my job. I am doing everything which I can to save my job. But I am not getting the desired output.\n\nI feel very helpless and many times I get depressed. I have one chance left to save my job. I will try my level best to give my best and perform good and save my job. But everything is in God's hand. I don't know what God has thought for me. May be he has some better plan for me. I don't know.\n\nBut I will really labour hard to save my job. I really don't want to lose my job. I want to do my best in this very job and make my parents proud.\n\nI request the Mathangs to pray to Lord Hanuman on my behalf to save my job just as they prayed for my job earlier.\n\nHanumanji, you know everything. You know how important this job is for me. You know what would happen if I lose this job. You know all the consequences. You gave me this job. Please don't take it away from me. If I have made any mistakes in this birth or previous births, please forgive me. Please help me become a good soul. And please please please Hanumanji, please save my job. I assure you I will labour hard but I need your blessings. Without you blessings, I can do nothing. Please bless me Hanumanji so that I can save my job.\n\nNowadays, I am very disturbed. Every time the question come to my mind what will I do if I lose my job. What will I do? These thoughts make me restless. I am not able to concentrate on my studies. I am losing my confidence. Bad thoughts come to my mind. This is my last attempt. This is the last chance for me to save my job. So, Hanumanji please give me strength and confidence so that I clear all my tests and save my job. Hanumanji, please keep your blessings on me forever. Please Prabhu bless me so that I perform well in my tests and save my job. Please show me the right path. Prabhu please do something that I start afresh today for my last attempt with much more zeal and complete my training.\n\nThsnks and regards.\n\nJai Bajrangbali.\nJai Shree Ram.",
